## Enumerations

### enum  {#a50a0bab21f1d14a86a1483ec283e4447}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::RTLIB::Libcall ">
<a href="#a50a0bab21f1d14a86a1483ec283e4447">RTLIB::Libcall</a> enum - This enum defines all of the runtime library calls the backend can emit.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

</EnumerationList>

The various long double types cannot be merged, because 80-bit library functions use &quot;xf&quot; and 128-bit use &quot;tf&quot;.

When adding PPCF128 functions here, note that their names generally need to be overridden for Darwin with the xxx$LDBL128 form. See <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/powerpc/ppcisellowering-cpp">PPCISelLowering.cpp</a>.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/runtimelibcalls-h/#l00033">33</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/runtimelibcalls-h">RuntimeLibcalls.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>
